<PB REF="65">
<HEAD>The ARGUMENT.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">The Di&s;covery of Uly&s;&s;es to Telemachus.</HEAD>
<P><HI>Telemachus</HI> arriving at the lodge of <HI>Eumaeus,</HI> &s;ends him to carry
<HI>Penelope</HI> the news of his return. <HI>Minerva</HI> appearing to <HI>Uly&s;|&s;es,</HI>
commands him to di&s;cover him&s;elf to his &s;on. The Princes,
who had lain in ambu&s;h to intercept <HI>Telemachus</HI> in his way,
their project being defeated, return to <HI>Ithaca.</HI></P>
