<L><PB N="252" REF="244">
The walls where-e'er my wond'ring &s;ight I turn,</L>
<L>And roofs, amid&s;t a blaze of glory burn!</L>
<L>Some vi&s;itant of pure etherial race,</L>
<L>With his bright pre&s;ence deigns the dome to grace.</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="50">Be calm, replies the Sire; to none impart,</L>
<L>But oft revolve the vi&s;ion in thy heart:</L>
<L>Cele&s;tials, mantl'd in exce&s;s of light,</L>
<L>Can vi&s;it unapproach'd by mortal &s;ight.</L>
